Sentencas: The cyclic voltammograms of strontium-doped lanthanum manganite (LSM) electrode as a function of temperature, oxygen partial pressure and potential scan rate were investigated in this study.
Titulo: Cyclic voltammetry of (La,Sr)MnO3 electrode on YSZ substrate

Sentencas: The current peaks corresponding to the reduction of LSM electrode materials and oxygen on the LSM surface were observed in the forward and backward scan.
Titulo: Cyclic voltammetry of (La,Sr)MnO3 electrode on YSZ substrate

Sentencas: The electrochemical process for the reduction of Mn3+ and the concomitant formation of oxygen vacancies is reversible (or quasi-reversible), which has become irreversible at low temperature or fast scan rate.
Titulo: Cyclic voltammetry of (La,Sr)MnO3 electrode on YSZ substrate

Sentencas: The improvement of LSM electrode performance under cathodic polarization and its gradual degradation after removal of applied potential were found to be related to two sequential reactions: reduction of Mn3+ to Mn2+ and recombination of Mn2+ with the formed oxygen vacancies in the presence of oxygen.
Titulo: Cyclic voltammetry of (La,Sr)MnO3 electrode on YSZ substrate

Sentencas: The oxygen reduction processes are strongly dependent on oxygen vacancies on the LSM electrode surface, which extend the reaction zone for oxygen reduction from three-phase boundary (TPB) to its vicinity under cathodic polarization.
Titulo: Cyclic voltammetry of (La,Sr)MnO3 electrode on YSZ substrate
